            <thetext>In a Python script that want to invoke a Python child process, it is better to 
use sys.executable in place of a literal &#39;python&#39; string. &#39;python&#39; hard-wires 
the name of the interpreter to use. This defeats using alternative interpreters 
across sub-process invocations.</thetext>
